{"kind":"blogger#post","id":"6084611055111877070","blog":{"id":"2360593805083673688"},"published":"2011-02-02T22:46:00-08:00","updated":"2011-02-02T23:25:58-08:00","url":"http://www.quietlikehorses.com/2011/02/afternoon-tea-at-mandarin-oriental-hong.html","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/6084611055111877070","title":"Afternoon Tea at the Mandarin Oriental, Hong Kong","content":"<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPaj99FNI/AAAAAAAAFF0/TZAPD6l_ql4/s1600/chocolate%2Btea.JPG\"><img style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPaj99FNI/AAAAAAAAFF0/TZAPD6l_ql4/s1600/chocolate%2Btea.JPG\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5569351206947329234\" border=\"0\" /></a>Ever since I was introduced to my friend Sashee (we met on a friendship blind date a mutual old boss set us up on), I've gotten a lot more into teas. I still start every morning with a good cup of coffee, but she's taught me to appreciate afternoon tea (as seen <a href=\"http://bit.ly/dNd21K\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://bit.ly/gRmDvU\">here</a>). So I jumped at the chance to have high tea at the <a href=\"http://bit.ly/etfLdV\">Mandarin Oriental</a> while we were in Hong Kong. The chocolate peppermint pot of tea, chocolate biscuits and tea sandwiches were a perfect way to relax after our morning hike, even if our outfits didn't come close to matching the sitting room's dress code of \"smart casual.\"<br />     <br /></div><a onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\" href=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPbHioXuI/AAAAAAAAFF8/iai5o3BayV8/s1600/tea%2Bsandwiche.JPG\"><img style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 600px; height: 400px;\" src=\"http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPbHioXuI/AAAAAAAAFF8/iai5o3BayV8/s1600/tea%2Bsandwiche.JPG\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5569351216496402146\" border=\"0\" /></a><br /><a onblur=\"try {parent.deselectBloggerImageGracefully();} catch(e) {}\" href=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPal-T-eI/AAAAAAAAFFs/FJHoUGnyLck/s1600/_SC_0187.JPG\"><img style=\"display: block; margin: 0px auto 10px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; width: 400px; height: 600px;\" src=\"http://2.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TUpPal-T-eI/AAAAAAAAFFs/FJHoUGnyLck/s1600/_SC_0187.JPG\" alt=\"\" id=\"BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5569351207485700578\" border=\"0\" /></a>","author":{"id":"06629562195146939698","displayName":"Sobrina Tung","url":"http://www.blogger.com/profile/06629562195146939698","image":{"url":"http://3.bp.blogspot.com/_mkw1MyhyGTY/TI8X4CO5nWI/AAAAAAAAERk/4p5D74gYdFE/S45/me.JPG"}},"replies":{"totalItems":"2","selfLink":"https://www.googleapis.com/blogger/v3/blogs/2360593805083673688/posts/6084611055111877070/comments"},"labels":["To Eat"]}